headline: Dell earnings, Sept. retail sales, jobless claims: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories to come out throughout next week, including quarterly earnings results from companies like Kohl's (KSS), Dell Technologies (DELL), and HP Inc. (HPQ); the release of September's delayed retail sales data and durable goods orders; and additional economic data, that includes initial jobless claims and pending home sales. Next week's trading week will be shortened with the stock market closed on Thursday for Thanksgiving and Friday's session ending early at 1 P.M. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
